					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/pedantique" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3118444); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3118444&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610205743" alt="Pedantique" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3118444)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/pedantique" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3118444); return false;" >Pedantique</a></span> <span class="odate time_1572486491 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">31 Oct 2019 01:48</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4410596">
									

<p>This sums up my own feelings perfectly. Interesting concept can't sustain something of this length, and verisimilitude doesn't make up for lack of interesting characters or plot elements. Every time I see this sort of thing executed, I'm exhausted by the fifth or sixth paragraphs. There's just nothing to sustain my interest or make me care as a reader.</p>

