					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/themightymcb" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4483018); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4483018&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610205743" alt="TheMightyMcB" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4483018)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/themightymcb" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4483018); return false;" >TheMightyMcB</a></span> <span class="odate time_1572453762 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">30 Oct 2019 16:42</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4410303">
									

<p>This was excellently written from an academic perspective and honestly that skill is commendable. Shit isn't easy, and I would know. This is the kind of writing that led to me writing SCPs in the first place, after all.</p>
<p>That being said, I'm finding myself very much in the same camp as gee here. This wasn't entertaining. I didn't enjoy reading, it didn't grab my attention, and I wouldn't voluntarily read this again. I don't think it's a good fit for the site, hence my downvote.</p>
<p>Let me be clear, this is good writing, but know that it's not a thing that I personally will likely ever enjoy.</p>

